cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a distributed model of programmable matter where particles operate and move on a hexagonal tasselation of the plane. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the movement of particles and their ability to form shapes. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper presents a new algorithm for the Shape-Formation problem. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the computational power of the particles and their ability to simulate a Turing-complete entity. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with a system of programmable particles and their ability to form shapes.
